@$VER: ARexx.guide 3.1 (7.11.99)
@AUTHOR Nils Görs, Moses Wildermuth, Robert Goodlett and Sebastian Bauer

@node main "SimpleFind's 3 ARexx Port"
@SMARTWRAP
@{b}ARexx Port@{ub}


SimpleFind3 supports a simple ARexx Port. With the ARexx Port you can use
SimpleFind's search capabilities from other programs.@{LINE}

The port's name is "SIMPLEFIND3.x", where x stands for the started SimpleFind3
process. If you start the ARexx-Script from SimpleFind3, RexxMast will set the
portname automatically to "SIMPLEFIND3.x". You can get the Portname with:@{LINE}
SFPort = ADDRESS()@{LINE}

In the functions below, arguments enclosed in "< >" are required, while those
enclosed in "[ ]" are optional.@{LINE}

SimpleFind3 provides the following ARexx Commands Additional to MUI's ARexx commands:@{LINE}
@{CODE}
@{" GET              " link AREXX_GET}   Get important things from SimpleFind3.
@{" SET              " link AREXX_SET}   Set important things of SimpleFind3.
@{" GETOPT           " link AREXX_GETOPT}   Get information of an search option.
@{" SETOPT           " link AREXX_SETOPT}   Set search options.
@{" LOCK             " link AREXX_LOCK}   (Un)Lock windows.
@{" SELECTENTRIES    " link AREXX_SELECTENTRIES}   Changes the state of the entries.

@{" REQUEST          " link AREXX_REQUEST}   Open a requester to wait for user response.
@{" STARTSEARCH      " link AREXX_STARTSEARCH}   Starts search process.
@{BODY}


You'll find some ARexx-Scripts in the SimpleFind3-release archiv:@{LINE}

@{" Index2Path.sfrx      " link //ARexx/Index2Path.sfrx/MAIN}@{LINE}
@{" Jump2NextMarked.sfrx " link //ARexx/Jump2NextMarked.sfrx/MAIN}@{LINE}
@{" Mark.sfrx            " link //ARexx/Mark.sfrx/MAIN}@{LINE}
@{" SaveEntries.sfrx     " link //ARexx/SaveEntries.sfrx/MAIN}@{LINE}
@{" SaveSelEntries.sfrx  " link //ARexx/SaveSelEntries.sfrx/MAIN}@{LINE}
@{" SFShell.sfrx         " link //ARexx/SFShell.sfrx/MAIN}@{LINE}
@{" SlideShow.sfrx       " link //ARexx/SlideShow.sfrx/MAIN}@{LINE}
@{" Vols2Path.sfrx       " link //ARexx/Vols2Path.sfrx/MAIN}@{LINE}

Thanks to Moses Wildermuth and Robert Goodlett for grammar checks.@{LINE}
@endnode


@NODE AREXX_GET "ARexx Command: GET"
@SMARTWRAP

@{b}Format:@{ub}@{LINE}
GET <TYPE/A>[VARNAME]@{LINE}

@{b}Template:@{ub}@{LINE}
GET TYPE/A,VARNAME@{LINE}


@{b}Description:@{ub}@{LINE}
Stores requested information in the RESULT variable and also in an optional ARexx Variable.@{LINE}


@{u}General Types:@{uu}@{LINE}
INDEXDIR	- the directory of the indexfiles.@{LINE}
INDEXFILES	- Names (not filenames!) of Indexfiles, stored in a given Stem-Var.@{LINE}
SEARCHGROUPS	- Stores all names from Searchgroup in a given Stem-Var.@{LINE}
                  RESULT and VARNAME.entries stores the number of entries.@{LINE}
SEARCHGROUPPOS	- Gives you the name of the current used searchgroup.@{LINE}
OPTIONSFILE	- Name and path of SimpleFind3 optionsfile.@{LINE}
PREFSFILE	- Name and path of SimpleFind3 prefsfile.@{LINE}
PROGDIR		- the directory where SimpleFind3 is located.@{LINE}
PUBSCREEN	- Name of public screen where SimpleFind3 windows are open.@{LINE}
REVISION	- the revision of SimpleFind3 (the number after the dot: 3.@{b}0@{ub})@{LINE}
UNPACKDIR	- the default unpack directory.@{LINE}
VERSION		- the version of SimpleFind3 (the number before the dot: @{b}3@{ub}.0)@{LINE}


@{u}Result Types:@{uu}@{LINE}
MARKERENTRY		- the information from the item under the cursor.@{LINE}
MARKERPOS		- the absolute position of the marker.@{LINE}
ENTRYPOS		- the absolute position of the entry cursor.@{LINE}
MAXFULLPATHLEN		- the length of the longest fullpath.@{LINE}
ENTRIES			- the number of all found entries.@{LINE}
ENTRY			- the information of the item under the entry cursor.@{LINE}
ENTRYNEXT		- the information of the item under the entry cursor.@{LINE}
			  the cursor is moved to the next entry.@{LINE}
ENTRYNEXTSEL		- the information of the item under the entry cursor.@{LINE}
			  the cursor is moved to the next selected entry.@{LINE}
FIRSTSELENTRYPOS	- the position of the first selected entry.@{LINE}
SELENTRIES		- the number of selected entries.@{LINE}
VISENTRIES		- the number of visible entries in result window.@{LINE}


@{b}Result:@{ub}@{LINE}
RESULT stores the requested information. Some commands use a given@{LINE}
stem-variable [VARNAME] to store additional information.@{LINE}

stem-vars for @{b}ENTRY@{ub}:@{LINE}
VARNAME.NAME		= Path and filename.@{LINE}
VARNAME.SIZE		= filesize.@{LINE}
VARNAME.COMMENT		= filecomment.@{LINE}
VARNAME.SECONDS		= seconds since 1978.@{LINE}
VARNAME.STATUS		= Status of entry: 0 deselected; 1 selected.@{LINE}
VARNAME.POSITION	= position.@{LINE}
VARNAME.PROTECTION	= protection-bits.@{LINE}

stem-vars for @{b}INDEXFILES@{ub}:@{LINE}
VARNAME.n.DIRECTORY	= stores the Indexname.@{LINE}
VARNAME.ENTRIES		= number of entries stored in the stem-var.@{LINE}

stem-vars for @{b}SEARCHGROUPS@{ub}:@{LINE}
VARNAME.n.GROUPNAME	= stores the name of searchgroup.@{LINE}
VARNAME.ENTRIES		= number of entries stored in the stem-var.@{LINE}


@{b}Notes:@{ub}@{LINE}
The entry in result and searchgroup window starts with @{b}0@{ub} not with @{b}1@{ub}.@{LINE}
If you are using SEARCHGROUPPOS or SEARCHGROUPS it is advice to @{"LOCK" link AREXX_LOCK} the window.@{LINE}


@{b}Examples:@{ub}@{LINE}
/*@{LINE}
  prints the name of each indexfile.@{LINE}
*/@{LINE}
options results@{LINE}

ADDRESS SIMPLEFIND3.1@{LINE}

GET INDEXFILES index@{LINE}
IF index.entries = 0 THEN EXIT@{LINE}
do i = 0 to index.entries-1@{LINE}
	say index.i@{LINE}
end@{LINE}
@endnode

@NODE AREXX_SET "ARexx Command: SET"
@SMARTWRAP

@{b}Format:@{ub}@{LINE}
SET <TYPE><VALUE>@{LINE}

@{b}Template@{ub}@{LINE}
SET TYPE/A,VALUE/A@{LINE}


@{b}Description:@{ub}@{LINE}
Assigns a new value to a given type.@{LINE}


@{u}General Types:@{uu}@{LINE}
SEARCHGROUPNAME	= activates the searchgroup with the name <VALUE>.@{LINE}
		  If the string <VALUE> does not exists RESULT will be @{b}-1@{ub}.@{LINE}

SEARCHGROUPPOS	= Uses the given Searchgroup. Entry starts with @{b}0@{ub}. If@{LINE}
		  you use DEFAULT as <VALUE> the "ģDefaultĢ" searchgroup@{LINE}
		  will be used.@{LINE}


@{b}Cursor/Marker control Types:@{ub}@{LINE}
ENTRYPOS	= <VALUE> could be a number to set the absolute position of the@{LINE}
		  entry cursor or alternativly you can specify one of the@{LINE}
		  following special keywords:@{LINE}

	TOP		= moves the entry cursor to the TOP of the list.@{LINE}
	BOTTOM		= moves the entry cursor to the BOTTOM of the list.@{LINE}
	TOPSELECTED	= moves the entry cursor to the first selected entry.@{LINE}
	BOTTOMSELECTED	= moves the entry cursor to the last selected entry.@{LINE}
	PREV		= moves the entry cursor one entry up.@{LINE}
	PREVSELECTED	= moves the entry cursor to the next selected entry@{LINE}
			  (direction: UP).@{LINE}
	NEXT		= moves the entry cursor one entry down.@{LINE}
	NEXTSELECTED	= moves the entry cursor to the next selected entry@{LINE}
			  (direction: DOWN).@{LINE}


MARKERPOS	= <VALUE> could be a number to set the absolute position of the@{LINE}
		  marker. Special meanings have the TOP and BOTTOM keyword.@{LINE}


@{b}Result:@{ub}@{LINE}
In RESULT you will get the new position of the entry/marker cursor or -1 if something went wrong.@{LINE}


@{b}Notes:@{ub}@{LINE}
The first entry in the result window starts with 0 not with 1.@{LINE}


@{b}Examples:@{ub}@{LINE}
/*@{LINE}
*/@{LINE}
options results@{LINE}

ADDRESS SIMPLEFIND3.1@{LINE}

set entrypos topselected@{LINE}
say result@{LINE}
@endnode

@NODE AREXX_GETOPT "ARexx Command: GETOPT"
@SMARTWRAP

@{b}Format:@{ub}@{LINE}
GETOPT <TYPE/A>[[CONTENTS]<VARNAME>][[SWITCH]<VARNAME>]@{LINE}

@{b}Template:@{ub}@{LINE}
GETOPT TYPE/A,CONTENTS,SWITCH@{LINE}


@{b}Description:@{ub}@{LINE}
Stores requested information about a search option in the given ARexx Variables.@{LINE}


@{b}Arguments:@{ub}@{LINE}
CONTENTS <VARNAME>	- <VARNAME> stores the contents of Search Option Types.@{LINE}
  SWITCH <VARNAME>	- <VARNAME> stores the status of Search Option Types@{LINE}
			   (@{b}1@{ub} if it's activated or @{b}0@{ub} if it's deactivated)@{LINE}


@{u}Search Option Types:@{uu}@{LINE}
PATH			= stores the path where SimpleFind3 should search for.@{LINE}
MAXDIRDEEP <1-50> or <OFF> = stores the maximum deep of directories where SimpleFind3 should search for.@{LINE}
NAME			= stores the pattern of the name search.@{LINE}
COMMENT			= stores the pattern of the comment search.@{LINE}
MINSIZE			= stores the minimum size of the files.@{LINE}
MAXSIZE			= stores the maximum size of the files.@{LINE}
WITHIN			= stores within which time span the files should have been created.@{LINE}
BETWEEN			= stores between which date the files.@{LINE}
PROTECTION		= stores the Protectionbits the files should have.@{LINE}
DATATYPE		= stores the files' datatype.@{LINE}
CONTENTS		= stores the text which should be in the file.@{LINE}


@{b}Result:@{ub}@{LINE}
RESULT stores the contents of the requested Search Option Types. CONTENTS <VARNAME>
is also stored in the RESULT variable.@{LINE}


@{b}Examples:@{ub}@{LINE}
/* Store the contents and the status of the Name option@{LINE}
   in NAMEPAT and NAMESTATUS@{LINE}
*/@{LINE}

GETOPT NAME "NAMEPAT" "NAMESTATUS"@{LINE}
say NAMEPAT@{LINE}
say NAMESTATUS@{LINE}


/* Get the contents of the Comment option inside the RESULT variable */@{LINE}
GETOPT COMMENT@{LINE}
@ENDNODE

@NODE AREXX_SETOPT "ARexx Command: SETOPT"
@SMARTWRAP

@{b}Format:@{ub}@{LINE}
SETOPT <TYPE/A>[CONTENTS][SWITCH/K][ACTIVATE/S]@{LINE}

@{b}Template:@{ub}@{LINE}
SETOPT TYPE/A,CONTENTS,SWITCH/K,ACTIVATE/S@{LINE}


@{b}Description:@{ub}@{LINE}
SETOPT sets the contents or change the status of a given option.


@{b}Arguments:@{ub}@{LINE}
SWITCH		- tells SimpleFind3 to use an option type or to@{LINE}
		  deactivate it, legal values for SWITCH are ON or OFF.@{LINE}

ACTIVATE	- sets the cursor in the string gadget, to prompt@{LINE}
		  the user to enter something.@{LINE}


@{b}Search Option Types:@{ub}@{LINE}
PATH			= Defines the path where SimpleFind3 should search for.@{LINE}
MAXDIRDEEP <1-50> or <ALL> = Defines the maximum deep of directories where SimpleFind3 should search for.@{LINE}
NAME			= Defines the pattern of the name search.@{LINE}
COMMENT			= Defines the pattern of the comment search.@{LINE}
MINSIZE			= Defines the minimum size of the files.@{LINE}
MAXSIZE			= Defines the maximum size of the files.@{LINE}
WITHIN			= Defines within which time span the files should have been created.@{LINE}
BETWEEN			= Defines between which date the files.@{LINE}
PROTECTION		= Defines the Protectionbits the files should have.@{LINE}
DATATYPE		= Defines the files' datatype.@{LINE}
CONTENTS		= Defines the text which should be in the file.@{LINE}


@{b}Examples:@{ub}@{LINE}

SETOPT NAME '""' ACTIVATE   /* clears the name string and activates the string gadget. */@{LINE}

SETOPT COMMENT SWITCH ON    /* Switch the status of comment to ON */@{LINE}
@ENDNODE

@NODE AREXX_LOCK "ARexx Command: LOCK"
@SMARTWRAP

@{b}Format:@{ub}@{LINE}
LOCK [RESULTS][SEARCHGROUPS][TEXT][OFF]@{LINE}

@{b}Template@{ub}@{LINE}
LOCK RESULTS/S,SEARCHGROUPS/S,TEXT,OFF/S@{LINE}


@{b}Description:@{ub}@{LINE}
Locks or unlocks a SimpleFind3 window. It is also possible to open a small
information window with a given text.@{LINE}


@{b}Arguments:@{ub}@{LINE}
RESULTS		locks the results window.@{LINE}

SEARCHGROUPS	locks the searchgroups window.@{LINE}

TEXT 		This is a @{b}one@{ub} line message text that will be@{LINE}
		displayed to tell the User why a window is locked.@{LINE}

OFF		unlocks a window lock.@{LINE}


@{b}Notes:@{ub}@{LINE}
It is possible to open a simple text-window without locking a window. To close this
text-window simply use the OFF argument.@{LINE}


@{b}Examples:@{ub}@{LINE}
LOCK RESULTS 'TEXT "Showing Pictures..."'@{LINE}

LOCK RESULTS OFF@{LINE}
@endnode

@NODE AREXX_SELECTENTRIES "ARexx Command: SELECTENTRIES"
@SMARTWRAP

@{b}Format:@{ub}@{LINE}
SELECTENTRIES [PATTERN][POS][ALL][TYPE]@{LINE}

@{b}Template:@{ub}@{LINE}
SELECTENTRIES PATTERN,POS/N/K,ALL/S,TYPE/K@{LINE}


@{b}Description:@{ub}@{LINE}
Selects or deselects all or some entries in the result window.@{LINE}


@{b}Arguments:@{ub}@{LINE}
PATTERN - AmigaOS Pattern which describes the files which should be selected.@{LINE}

POS	- the position of the entry which should be selected (PATTERN is ignored)@{LINE}

ALL	- all files should be selected (PATTERN and POS are ignored)@{LINE}

TYPE	- either ON (to select), OFF (to deselect) or TOGGLE (to invert the state)@{LINE}


@{b}Examples:@{ub}@{LINE}
SELECTENTRIES ALL			/* selects all entries */@{LINE}

SELECTENTRIES ALL TYPE OFF		/* deselects all entries */@{LINE}
@endnode

@NODE AREXX_REQUEST "ARexx Command: REQUEST"
@SMARTWRAP

@{b}Format:@{ub}@{LINE}
REQUEST <BODY/A/K>[GADGETS/K][TITLE/K]@{LINE}

@{b}Template@{ub}@{LINE}
REQUEST BODY/A/K,GADGETS/K,TITLE/K@{LINE}


@{b}Description:@{ub}@{LINE}
This command opens a requester for you and then waits for a response from the user.@{LINE}


@{b}Arguments:@{ub}@{LINE}
BODY     the body text (required). This is the main text that@{LINE}
	 is displayed in the requester. If you want to use a@{LINE}
	 "%"-character in body text you'll have to type "%%".@{LINE}
	 You can split this text on several lines by using "\\n".@{LINE}

GADGETS  the gadget text (optional, defaults to " OK ").@{LINE}
	 Each gadget is separated  from the others@{LINE}
	 by a bar character  ("|").@{LINE}
	 You can also specify a shortcut for each gadget@{LINE}
	 by placing an underscore ("_") before the character@{LINE}
	 that identifies the shortcut key.@{LINE}

TITLE    title of the requester (optional).@{LINE}


@{b}Result:@{ub}@{LINE}
The RESULT variable is either TRUE or FALSE. If you generate a requester
with more than one response button the RESULT for the leftmost (positive)
response will be 1, then  each  consecutive response  will return 1 more,
the rightmost (false) response will return 0 (false), so 1,2,3,...,0@{LINE}


@{b}Notes:@{ub}@{LINE}
As long as the requester is open, all user activities are limited to the requester.
REQUEST is not limited to an opened result window.@{LINE}


@{b}Examples:@{ub}@{LINE}
'REQUEST BODY "Please press a button!" GADGETS "_1|_2|_3|_No" TITLE "I''m a testprogram"'@{LINE}
say result@{LINE}

REQUEST 'BODY="No selected entries!"'@{LINE}
@endnode

@NODE AREXX_STARTSEARCH "ARexx Command: STARTSEARCH"
@SMARTWRAP

@{b}Format:@{ub}@{LINE}
STARTSEARCH [SYNC/S] [APPEND/S]@{LINE}

@{b}Template:@{ub}@{LINE}
STARTSEARCH SYNC/S,APPEND/S@{LINE}


@{b}Description:@{ub}@{LINE}
Starts search process with the setted options.@{LINE}


@{b}Arguments:@{ub}@{LINE}
SYNC   Waits until the search has been finished.@{LINE}
APPEND Adds the found files at a existing list.@{LINE}
@endnode

